&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSEX PARTNERSHIP UNIVERSITY TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LEARNING DISABILITY SERVICES ESSEX&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behaviour Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.0 WTE Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LD Psychology Community Services in South Essex&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based in Billericay, Essex &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint a full time Band 6 Behaviour Therapist to join the Learning Disabilities Psychology and Behaviour Therapy services in Essex, based in South Essex as part of the community team and Essex Learning Disability Partnership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from highly motivated and resourceful individuals who are keen to work as part of a team. The newly appointed Behaviour Therapist will be joining a well-established Psychology and Behaviour Therapy team as well as multi-disciplinary community service. The MDT consists of nursing, physio and occupational therapy, speech and language therapy, and psychiatry. The wider service is developing further and is part of a partnership with local Trusts in an Essex wide Learning Disability Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will have a management role in supporting and supervising the existing Behaviour Therapy Team in conjunction with the LD Psychology Lead. The clinical responsibilities will be in utilising behaviour therapy as an approach, including PBS, for adults with learning disabilities living in the community. This work will be with individuals directly as well as family, carers and support staff. Strong engagement skills and the ability to work creatively in relation to behaviour that challenges and complex multi-agency networks are essential. We are seeking candidates with a commitment to evidence-based practice, service development, client and carer participation and utilising outcome measures. Clinical supervision will be provided by a Senior Clinical Psychologist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Experience required: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diploma or degree level training in Behaviour Therapy and evidence of supporting staff in a line management/supervision capacity. Experience of working with a wide variety of client groups with presenting problems that reflect the full range of clinical severity as well as specific experience of LD services both inpatient and community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The county of Essex is geographically close to London with good transport links to the East Anglia region, it has a more affordable standard of living than London itself, making it an attractive place to live and work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return of your commitment, the Trust offers a wide range of training opportunities and career development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal queries and visits are welcome&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date for applications: 20 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be scheduled to take place in November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to talk to somebody about this vacancy then please contact Sharon Allison, Consultant Clinical Psychologist/Head of Aspergers Service and Learning Disabilities Psychology Tel: 07940449874.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
